<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Defiance" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Defiance,</orth> 1) challenge to fight: <bibl n="shak. jn 1.21" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.130" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.2.43" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 2, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 3.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B III, 1, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.4.117" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 4, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.5.37" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 37</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.142" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 1, 64</bibl>. <cit><quote>to fill the mouth of deep d. up,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.116" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 116</bibl></cit> (or perhaps == feud, enmity?).<lb />2) rejection, declaration that one will have nothing to do with another: <cit><quote>take my d.! die, perish!</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 143</bibl></cit>.
